
MDM - MATE Display Manager
http://www.gnome.org/projects/mdm/

The MATE Display Manager is a system service that is responsible for
providing graphical log-ins and managing local and remote displays.


Installation
============

See the file 'INSTALL'.


How to report bugs
==================

Bugs should be reported to the MATE bug tracking
system:
    http://bugzilla.gnome.org/simple-bug-guide.cgi?product=mdm

You will need to create an account if you don't have one already.

Please read the following page on how to prepare a useful
bug report:
    http://bugzilla.gnome.org/bug-HOWTO.html


How to submit patches
=====================

See the file 'HACKING'.
